Setophaga discolor is a species of small, migratory songbird.
Its body length ranges from 11 to 14 centimeters and has a wingspan of about 20 centimeters.
The head, back and wings are blackish-blue in color, while the underparts are whitish-yellow.
The throat and upper breast areas exhibit a yellow-orange coloration.
Setophaga discolor can be found in various parts of North America during breeding season and South America during wintering season.
Its preferred habitats include open woodlands, forests, and areas with scattered shrubs.
These birds are known for their energetic and acrobatic foraging behaviors.
